time datetime=\u00222018-03-09T16:25:44Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 04:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by The Dunatian\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:25:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you simply stop it from transmitting by switching the internet connection off on your computer or router?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShort of a sledgehammer to the CPU, that would be the nuclear option, yes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:26:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612739\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShort of a sledgehammer to the CPU, that would be the nuclear option, yes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent then. Assuming that it\u0027s only up to mischeif when the game is running.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T16:27:15Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 04:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by The Dunatian\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:28:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDISCLAIMER: I don\u0027t mean to fuel a fire or start an argument, I\u0027m just new to this and slightly confused. If this does something along those lines I\u0027ll take it down myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost websites on the planet collects data, from the Book of Face to gaming sites. Why does it all of a sudden matter if TT2 states that they \u003Cu\u003Emay\u003C/u\u003E take some of \u00A0our data? And even if they do, other sites already do it too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T16:30:50Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 04:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by nascarlaser1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EThe language I was born with is native to me aparently XD\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:28:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you simply stop it from transmitting by switching the internet connection off on your computer or router?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo the EULA says they\u0027ll gather it all now, and phone home\u00A0later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd one might assume they\u0027ll start a \u0022licence check\u0022 on startup that requires inet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:31:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t you simply stop it from transmitting by switching the internet connection off on your computer or router?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven better is to use a good firewall. I like this one. \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.sphinx-soft.com/Vista/order.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EWindows 10 Firewall Control\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDespite the name, it works on Vista, 7, 8 and 10, in both 32 and 64 bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:32:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314639\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nascarlaser1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, nascarlaser1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost websites on the planet collects data, from the books of Face to gaming sites. Why does it all of a sudden matter if TT2 states that they \u003Cu\u003Emay\u003C/u\u003E take some of \u00A0our data? And even if they do, other sites already do it too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u0022We\u0027ve made too many compromises already; too many retreats. They invade our space and we fall back. They assimilate entire worlds and we fall back. Not again. The line must be drawn here! This far, no further!\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:33:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314644\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520613081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132901\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JAFO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, JAFO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven better is to use a good firewall. I like this one. \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.sphinx-soft.com/Vista/order.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EWindows 10 Firewall Control\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDespite the name, it works on Vista, 7, 8 and 10, in both 32 and 64 bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill something like Norton firewall work as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612789\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent then. Assuming that it\u0027s only up to mischeif when the game is running.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose are two different assumptions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour first comment was if disconnecting the computer from the internet would prevent it from talking to the internet.\u00A0 I said yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour second comment is that it only transmits only when KSP is running.\u00A0 To that, I have no idea.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:34:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314639\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nascarlaser1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, nascarlaser1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost websites on the planet collects data, from the Book of Face to gaming sites. Why does it all of a sudden matter if TT2 states that they \u003Cu\u003Emay\u003C/u\u003E take some of \u00A0our data? And even if they do, other sites already do it too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause until now, KSP had avoided this kind of behaviour..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s sad to see them follow the rest swirling down the toilet bowl.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:36:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520613265\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132901\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JAFO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, JAFO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause until now, KSP had avoided this kind of behaviour..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s sad to see them follow the rest swirling down the toilet bowl.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhen I first got KSP, it asked me on start up if I was ok with them doing it, and each time I\u0027ve updated\u00A0though (This was 1.0,and I\u0027ve yet to get 1.4).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr. Peabody","CreatedById":173591,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:37:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520613176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110905\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brainlord Mesomorph\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Brainlord Mesomorph said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u0022We\u0027ve made too many compromises already; too many retreats. They invade our space and we fall back. They assimilate entire worlds and we fall back. Not again. The line must be drawn here! This far, no further!\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Thin_Red_Line_(Battle_of_Balaclava)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Thin_Red_Line_(Battle_of_Balaclava)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520613176\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110905\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brainlord Mesomorph\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Brainlord Mesomorph said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u0022We\u0027ve made too many compromises already; too many retreats. They invade our space and we fall back. They assimilate entire worlds and we fall back. Not again. The line must be drawn here! This far, no further!\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBugger this damn limit on likes.. would someone \u0022like\u0022 to do the honours for me? This one\u0027s a seriously good point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314649\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520613185\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173591\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Dunatian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, The Dunatian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill something like Norton firewall work as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe.. I don\u0027t know how granular it is. Nortons is far too much of a resource hog, IMO, and I avoid it. Can you control outgoing connections on a per-program and/or URL basis?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you already have it, give it a try.. if you don\u0027t, don\u0027t go buying it for this use alone. The one I linked to is free, and has even more features if you buy it. But the free version is excellent as-is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheif Operations Director","CreatedById":183218,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:48:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI almost always read the EULAs and this is the one time did not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the EULA say they wont sell your information? I don\u0027t remember it saying that. As much as I love KSP I\u0027m not going to compromise my entire life for it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheCardinal","CreatedById":22874,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:50:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314661\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520613572\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132901\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JAFO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, JAFO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBugger this damn limit on likes.. would someone \u0022like\u0022 to do the honours for me? This one\u0027s a seriously good point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDone!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:53:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314639\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520612914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nascarlaser1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, nascarlaser1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost websites on the planet collects data, from the Book of Face to gaming sites. Why does it all of a sudden matter if TT2 states that they \u003Cu\u003Emay\u003C/u\u003E take some of \u00A0our data? And even if they do, other sites already do it too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would be very surprised if there was a website which didn\u0027t log requests - and most of them will log referral data with that so they know where the request came from. Been like that since day zero, pretty much. On top of that, ISPs running transparent proxies will also be logging requests as a matter of course ( and even if they\u0027re not transparent ). This is all before we start going into packet inspection and other issues which are also a matter of routine. The price you pay for using the internet is someone knowing what you\u0027re doing - if nobody knew what you\u0027re doing at all the whole system wouldn\u0027t work, because it\u0027s a system which uses cooperative transfer of data.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway this is a non-issue technically, just firewall the game. Ethically, *shrug*, see above.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-09T16:54:44Z\u0022 title=\u002203/09/2018 04:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Van Disaster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-09T16:56:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223314682\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520614423\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Van Disaster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Van Disaster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would be very surprised if there was a website which didn\u0027t log requests - and most of them will log referral data with that so they know where the request came from. Been like that since day zero, pretty much. On top of that, ISPs running transparent proxies will also be logging requests as a matter of course ( and even if they\u0027re not transparent ). This is all before we start going into packet inspection and other issues which are also a matter of routine. The price you pay for using the internet is someone knowing what you\u0027re doing - if nobody knew what you\u0027re doing at all the whole system wouldn\u0027t work, because it\u0027s a system which uses cooperative transfer of data.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway this is a non-issue technically, just firewall the game. Ethically, *shrug*, see above.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh ok thank you \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}